2013-01-01|2013-12-30.description:
Emiko is a broken girl. Her art expresses the horror and violence she holds close to her with gore filled imagery of sexual revenge. Men who take innocence face the slashing and bloody vengeance they deserve in the pages of 'Gore Angels.' But when the Crossed begin to spread, the world itself is transformed into a mockery of her art. And among the gleeful monsters, there are precious few places to hide from the misery of the Crossed.

Available with a Regular cover by Jacen Burrows, Torture cover by Matt Martin, Wraparound cover by Rafael Ortiz, and special Red Crossed Incentive cover by Burrows.

After their umpteenth defeat at Lucky Luke’s hands, the Dalton brothers get into a big argument that ends with the four of them splitting up. They make a deal: Whoever is first to get a million dollars will be the leader of the gang. Going their separate ways, trying various schemes, each spreads his own kind of mayhem, forcing poor Lucky Luke to do four times the work to keep up with their antics!

2013-01-01|2013-12-30.description:
In Black Jack: False Image, Black Jack attends an elementary school reunion! Former classmates from far and wide attend, but the biggest guest of honor is out sick: the beloved teacher Mr. Shima. Black Jack is tasked with finding the reclusive man, but what plagues Shima is not illness, but addiction. Can Shima recover in time for a reunion with his former students? Also included are Astro Boy, Buddha, and Phoenix.

2013-01-01|2013-12-30.description: Alex Ross discusses his daily routine of working from a home studio. They move into his methods of creating some on modern days iconic comic book masterpieces and how he believes today's publishers could bring a better product to the consumer. Sketch continues to satisfy with numerous "how-to" instructional from tried-and-true industry talent, and is packed with penciling, computer coloring, and marketing tips to help you become an artistic rising star.
Translates Red Hood and the Outlaws #15-16, Teen Titans #15-16, Suicide Squad #14-15, Detective Comics #16 & Batman #13-15.

Take a ride in a flying saucer with Cosmo the Merry Martian! For the first time ever, this classic interplanetary tale has been collected into one giant-size collection.
